Vice President Joe Biden made calls to U.S. Ambassador to Iraq Chris Hill, U.S. Forces-Iraq Commanding General Ray Odierno, Iraqi President Jalal Talabani, and Iraqi Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki to discuss recent developments in Iraq. He conveyed sympathy and condolences for the victims of recent attacks and expressed confidence in the capabilities of the Iraqi Security Forces. The Vice President reiterated U.S. readiness to provide support and stated his belief that the Iraqis will not be deterred from moving forward. He also emphasized respect for Iraqi sovereignty and encouraged all sides to work together to form an inclusive and representative government.